    "cost_rationale": "This workflow requires multi-tool orchestration at multiple stages: (1) IAM role check is a straightforward single-table query (small tier sql_gen); (2) fetching manager approval involves querying a workflow system likely outside the standard SQL/MongoDB warehouse, requiring multitool_plan to route to the appropriate workflow API (mid tier for moderate integration complexity); (3) updating IAM permissions requires coordinating with multiple identity/access control systems (multitool_plan, mid tier) and depends on the approval result; (4) email confirmation is a simple notification task (multitool_plan, small tier) that depends on successful permission updates. The workflow is decomposed into 4 subtasks because each represents a distinct operational step with different system dependencies and handoff points. Combining IAM check with approval fetch or email would mask important workflow orchestration points.\""
